"\ud83d\udcf0 Faysal Bank (FABL) has announced its financial results for the year ended December 31, 2023, with earnings per share (EPS) of Rs13.34, compared to Rs7.54 in the same period last year. The bank has also reported a sharp increase in expenditure on worker welfare fund, which almost doubled during the period. \ud83d\udcb0\n\nIn other news, FABL has announced the establishment of an exchange company as a wholly-owned subsidiary, in line with the Pakistan Stock Exchange's (PSX) directive to commercial banks to set up exchange companies. \ud83d\udcc8\n\nAdditionally, other banks in Pakistan, such as Askari Bank and JS Bank, have also established exchange companies as wholly-owned subsidiaries. \ud83d\udcbc\n\nMeanwhile, Islamic banks in Pakistan have come under scrutiny due to concerns about insufficient returns on deposits. A research report by JS Global highlights that Islamic banks are currently offering savings rates that are between 7-9.5 percentage points lower than the minimum deposit rate (MDR) offered by conventional banks. \ud83d\udcb8\n\nFurthermore, FABL has been positioned as a key player in Pakistan's Islamic banking sector, with a"